WEBVTT

00:05.793 --> 00:08.220
A well-run company is like
an intricate machine.

00:08.345 --> 00:12.625
A lot of moving parts working together
in perfect precision.

00:17.444 --> 00:20.876
You might say Veridian Dynamics
is like a finely tuned watch.

00:20.976 --> 00:24.462
That's Dale. He even has
a big hand and a little hand.

00:24.562 --> 00:27.268
You guys are great.
Ahead of schedule and under budget.

00:27.368 --> 00:28.505
So what is it?

00:28.630 --> 00:31.072
We call it "The voice of God."

00:31.449 --> 00:33.446
No, we don't.
- No, we don't.

00:33.546 --> 00:35.774
Hypersonic sound, or H.S,

00:35.994 --> 00:37.814
projects a narrow beam of sound

00:37.914 --> 00:40.882
which can only be heard
by a specifically targeted person.

00:40.982 --> 00:43.352
Field testing shows
that the subject, or "victim,"

00:43.452 --> 00:46.462
as I like to call people "helped"
by Veridian technology,

00:46.562 --> 00:48.683
can be hundreds of feet away
and will hear the message

00:48.783 --> 00:50.701
as thought it's being whispered
only to them.

00:50.801 --> 00:52.361
It's highly persuasive.

00:52.389 --> 00:54.305
Advertising companies
are very excited

00:54.405 --> 00:56.718
because it will allow them
to burrow even deeper

00:56.818 --> 00:58.318
into the human brain.

00:59.845 --> 01:02.880
Let's zap Rick.
He's always using the copy machine.

01:02.980 --> 01:05.871
We get it.
You need to make a lot of copies.

01:05.971 --> 01:07.951
Just don't set it too high.

01:08.003 --> 01:10.066
At full power,
the sound wave is so intense,

01:10.166 --> 01:11.513
it can cause vomiting.

01:11.613 --> 01:13.164
A machine that causes vomiting.

01:13.264 --> 01:16.101
that could have all kinds
of applications for the military...

01:16.201 --> 01:17.728
And fashion modeling.

01:19.623 --> 01:21.437
It's me... God.

01:23.788 --> 01:26.568
You want me
to stop using the copier?

01:27.485 --> 01:30.385
But why?
I don't make that many copies.

01:32.303 --> 01:34.283
No, I'm not questioning you.

01:35.564 --> 01:39.304
This is what it would be like
if god was insecure.

01:42.680 --> 01:45.097
This place may be
a perfectly tuned machine,

01:45.197 --> 01:46.982
but the thing about
a perfect machine,

01:47.082 --> 01:51.662
it only takes the smallest glitch
to throw the whole thing off.

