contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:03.966 --> 02:05.536
That's not right.

02:17.102 --> 02:18.466
Really not right.

02:23.936 --> 02:25.556
This is such a circus.

02:26.246 --> 02:28.175
You're a baby, you know that?

02:28.275 --> 02:30.631
A big baby.
- Veronica, it's toxic.

02:30.731 --> 02:32.655
We had to call in
the contamination guys.

02:32.755 --> 02:36.772
Am I allowed to ask what ate my desk?
- All we know is it came from a leak

02:36.872 --> 02:39.193
from Dr. Bhamba's biocomputer
upstairs.

02:39.293 --> 02:42.583
A biocomputer.
It's half machine, half living organism.

02:42.683 --> 02:45.588
If you think that sounds creepy,
you should see it at feeding time.

02:45.688 --> 02:48.768
Speaking of useless,
half-living organisms...

02:49.695 --> 02:52.082
I brought doughnuts...
A festive treat

02:52.182 --> 02:54.408
while we wait out
this little inconvenience.

02:54.508 --> 02:57.086
Don't think you can buy
your way out of this with doughnuts,

02:57.186 --> 02:59.286
Just give me a status report.

02:59.307 --> 03:01.227
Okay, and a buttermilk log.

03:01.635 --> 03:02.832
The biocomputer,

03:02.957 --> 03:05.857
which I have humorously
named "Johnny"...

03:09.162 --> 03:10.970
Has been leaking an acid-like goo,

03:11.070 --> 03:12.593
or "ass-goo," for short.

03:12.693 --> 03:13.937
Anyway, we're stumped.

03:14.037 --> 03:15.993
Johnny has been running nonstop
for three years,

03:16.093 --> 03:18.006
and we've never had a problem
like this before.

03:18.106 --> 03:21.524
Sadly, until we find the reason
for the leak, it will continue.

03:21.624 --> 03:23.955
Is it even safe to work
in the building?

03:24.055 --> 03:25.375
Just get it fixed.

03:25.957 --> 03:28.057
And you need to grow a pair.

03:29.459 --> 03:32.059
<i>Veronica assigned Dr. Bhamba
to room 4-d,</i>

03:32.159 --> 03:35.839
<i>which is known as
"the ridiculously tiny office."</i>

03:39.303 --> 03:41.583
This office is ridiculously tiny.

03:45.059 --> 03:47.773
<i>Other employees were left
to find their own office space.</i>

03:47.873 --> 03:50.075
People, people!
- Please, help us!

03:50.175 --> 03:52.815
I hate seeing you put out like this.

03:53.911 --> 03:57.329
I said, I hate seeing you
put out like this.

04:02.189 --> 04:03.124
Thank you.

04:04.077 --> 04:06.917
Make sure that it...
It's more powdery.

04:07.017 --> 04:09.082
I'm supposed to share
an office with Wallace,

04:09.182 --> 04:11.149
that food-taster guy
in the basement.

04:11.249 --> 04:13.469
Unless anyone else has an idea?

04:14.718 --> 04:17.498
Take the freight elevator?
It's faster.

04:17.793 --> 04:18.632
Thanks.

04:18.800 --> 04:21.880
That's exactly the idea
I was looking for.

04:24.072 --> 04:25.843
I don't know anything about women...

04:25.943 --> 04:29.443
At least, according to my wife...
But I think...

04:29.587 --> 04:33.297
Linda wants to move into your office.
- I know, but it'd be awkward.

04:33.397 --> 04:35.892
Even though she has a boyfriend,
there's always been this...

04:35.992 --> 04:37.492
Attraction between us.

04:37.796 --> 04:39.776
I mean, she is smokin' hot.

04:40.538 --> 04:44.062
Anyway, you're right, but
I just don't think it's a good idea.

04:44.162 --> 04:46.291
So I do know something about women.

04:46.391 --> 04:48.132
I am gonna call my wife

04:48.409 --> 04:50.789
and tell her how hot Linda is.

04:52.096 --> 04:53.143
Oh, wait.

05:00.927 --> 05:03.227
Experimental cracker?
- God. No.

05:03.520 --> 05:05.125
But you keep chewing.

05:11.927 --> 05:12.806
Pretty.

05:17.150 --> 05:21.329
Maybe I wasn't being that clear before.
Can I move in with you?

05:21.429 --> 05:23.857
But what about Wallace
and all his crazy foods?

05:23.957 --> 05:25.397
That's gotta be fun.

05:26.428 --> 05:28.628
He told me he needs
a good woman in his life

05:28.728 --> 05:30.468
cause his mom just died.

05:30.512 --> 05:33.394
Then he coughed up some of
the experimental cracker he's eating

05:33.494 --> 05:34.912
and swal lowed it again.

05:35.012 --> 05:38.080
I mean, sure, every girl dreams
of a romantic moment like that,

05:38.180 --> 05:40.580
but it was all happening so fast.

05:41.288 --> 05:43.560
Well, I'd love to help you, Linda,

05:43.660 --> 05:47.622
but I don't have a big office.
- In here. In here... In here...

05:47.722 --> 05:49.882
And there's that terrible echo.

05:51.583 --> 05:54.425
Of course. I'd be happy
to have you share my office.

05:54.525 --> 05:56.685
Thank you. I'll be right back.

05:57.774 --> 06:01.421
And your pen-holder's gonna be perfect
for my tampons.

06:01.521 --> 06:02.433
I'm kidding.

06:02.558 --> 06:06.178
But seriously,
I'm gonna need a couple of drawers.

06:06.611 --> 06:08.851
I can do this.
It'll be fine.

06:08.878 --> 06:12.978
We'll just have to make sure
we keep things professional.

06:18.138 --> 06:21.998
God, I've been lugging that thing
all over the place.

06:30.695 --> 06:31.699
Oh, boy.

06:35.969 --> 06:36.952
<i>Machines...</i>

06:37.699 --> 06:40.152
<i>When you were little,
you wanted to be one.</i>

06:40.252 --> 06:42.845
<i>Now we're working
to make that happen</i>

06:42.945 --> 06:45.905
<i>by taking the best things
about people</i>

06:45.943 --> 06:48.783
<i>and the best things
about machines...</i>

06:50.548 --> 06:51.905
<i>And combing them</i>

06:52.364 --> 06:53.816
<i>into something strong</i>

06:53.916 --> 06:55.716
<i>and, we hope, loving...</i>

07:06.014 --> 07:10.122
<i>I wasn't the only one being affected
by the goo coming out of Johnny.</i>

07:10.222 --> 07:12.324
<i>All the scientists from
the biocomputer floor</i>

07:12.424 --> 07:14.124
<i>had been reassigned to other labs. </i>

07:14.224 --> 07:16.890
Why don't you go talk to her?
- Talk to her?

07:16.990 --> 07:19.778
Would you talk to a rainbow
or a sunset?

07:19.878 --> 07:22.759
If I wanted to get it on
with refracted light, I would.

07:22.859 --> 07:24.479
If only I was a worm.

07:24.527 --> 07:26.763
I could cut myself in two
and date my lower half.

07:26.863 --> 07:28.660
We all wish we were worms, Lem,

07:28.760 --> 07:32.500
but that's never going to happen.
Now get in there.

07:41.179 --> 07:42.124
I'm Lem.

07:43.077 --> 07:45.857
I'm lucy.
I work upstairs in robotics.

07:46.967 --> 07:48.488
I shouldn't be talking to you.

07:48.588 --> 07:52.508
I just created a robot-boyfriend
who gets very jealous.

07:52.889 --> 07:54.305
Wait. I'm kidding.

07:54.973 --> 07:55.933
We broke up.

07:56.864 --> 07:58.811
That's funny.
You're funny.

07:59.497 --> 08:00.846
I can be funny.

08:01.493 --> 08:04.867
Want to see me throw something
at that guy or touch the ceiling?

08:04.967 --> 08:06.223
That's lame.

08:07.320 --> 08:11.000
But it's cute you're trying
so hard to impress me.

08:11.375 --> 08:13.409
You should meet me
for a drink tonight

08:13.509 --> 08:17.609
after I've dinner with my mom
and pretend to go to bed.

08:17.680 --> 08:18.878
<i>One drip on a desk.</i>

08:18.978 --> 08:21.970
<i>That's all it took
to throw things out of whack.</i>

08:22.070 --> 08:26.710
<i>And when that happens,
it changes the way you look at things.</i>

08:28.690 --> 08:30.670
Are you staring at my butt?

08:32.330 --> 08:34.337
No, your butt
is in my staring place.

08:34.437 --> 08:36.707
So technically, it's staring at me.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.048
Sorry.
It's from a small town.

08:39.142 --> 08:41.787
It's never seen a big businessman
like you before.

08:41.886 --> 08:43.870
Well, tell it to act
more professional.

08:43.970 --> 08:46.370
It's making a spectacle of itself.

08:54.592 --> 08:57.605
I was worried about sharing an office
with someone I'm attracted to,

08:57.705 --> 08:58.836
but the problem

08:58.961 --> 09:01.719
is being stuck with someone
with such annoying work habits.

09:01.819 --> 09:03.958
Mama. Say...

09:08.423 --> 09:12.703
Look, he's trying to say it,
only he pronounces it Maw-maw.

09:14.027 --> 09:14.982
Excuse me.

09:16.139 --> 09:18.333
I need to get some word one.
Maybe you should also.

09:18.433 --> 09:20.715
And I'm sure the fish
has things to do, too,

09:20.815 --> 09:23.046
like protect his treasure
from that diver.

09:23.146 --> 09:25.786
First of all, "the fish" has a name.

09:25.816 --> 09:26.899
He's Macgyver.

09:27.067 --> 09:29.401
That's right...
Macgyver and the diver.

09:29.501 --> 09:31.494
And second of all,
they're gay-married.

09:31.594 --> 09:34.153
And don't you dare judge...
- You do know I need your report

09:34.253 --> 09:37.225
on the hypersonic sound project
in two days?

09:37.325 --> 09:39.485
Look who's all, "get to work."

09:40.864 --> 09:43.321
Macgyver, why do you think
Ted's like that?

09:43.421 --> 09:46.546
Who do you think
he didn't get enough love from?

09:46.646 --> 09:48.566
That's right... His maw-maw.

09:49.632 --> 09:51.000
<i>Are you ready?</i>

09:51.823 --> 09:52.842
<i>I'm ready.</i>

09:53.335 --> 09:54.743
<i>Are you ready?</i>

09:55.655 --> 09:56.687
<i>I'm ready.</i>

09:56.867 --> 09:58.547
<i>Is your report ready?</i>

09:58.862 --> 10:00.422
<i>No, it's not ready.</i>

10:00.517 --> 10:05.097
<i>- I should have your fish do it
- He can only write "mama"</i>

10:06.745 --> 10:08.675
I had a great time last night.

10:08.775 --> 10:11.915
I've never been
to a dance-aoke bar before.

10:12.237 --> 10:13.953
Technically, it's a karaoke bar,

10:14.053 --> 10:16.953
but I like to bring it
when I perform.

10:17.121 --> 10:17.949
Listen,

10:18.119 --> 10:23.059
I had a great time also. I'm just
so sorry about the way it ended.

10:25.512 --> 10:26.652
Good night, Lem.

10:27.474 --> 10:28.502
Good night.

10:36.094 --> 10:38.374
You were allergic to my perfume.

10:38.532 --> 10:40.692
It could've happened to anyone.

10:41.806 --> 10:43.801
I'm not wearing any now.

10:48.061 --> 10:49.194
How you doin'?

10:49.319 --> 10:52.339
I'm Brody.
I was assigned to this office.

10:52.786 --> 10:55.066
With this beautiful, exotic lady.

10:55.360 --> 10:57.381
I'm not exotic.
I'm asian.

10:57.877 --> 11:00.171
There are more of us
than there are of you,

11:00.271 --> 11:02.563
so statistically,
you're the exotic one.

11:02.663 --> 11:04.929
What? Wait... What?

11:05.521 --> 11:08.421
You heard
the statistically average lady.

11:12.951 --> 11:14.943
Is it possible
to overdose on antacid?

11:15.043 --> 11:16.311
I hope the answer's yes.

11:16.411 --> 11:18.406
Here. Let's find out together.

11:18.506 --> 11:20.497
They just yelled at me upstairs.

11:20.597 --> 11:23.862
They're mad because this leak is hurting
productivity in our department.

11:23.962 --> 11:26.071
Someone even suggested making
the cubicle workers

11:26.171 --> 11:28.421
do their jobs in hazmat suits.
- That seems a little...

11:28.521 --> 11:30.428
Save your breath.
They told me no.

11:30.528 --> 11:32.748
I need this leak fixednow, Ted.

11:33.109 --> 11:35.065
I'm not waiting on Bhamba.
He's so stressed,

11:35.165 --> 11:38.776
he spends his day staring out the window
he drew on the wall of his office.

11:38.876 --> 11:40.978
I put Lem and Phil on it.
Believe me,

11:41.078 --> 11:43.838
no one wants this problem solved
more than I do.

11:43.938 --> 11:48.087
Is Ken having trouble with Barbie
in their Malibu dream house?

11:48.187 --> 11:50.903
I must say, the thought of you guys
in there together sickens me.

11:51.003 --> 11:52.085
You're jealous?

11:52.325 --> 11:55.340
Jealous implies I can't have
something I want.

11:55.440 --> 11:58.607
This is more like
if someone borrows my stapler...

11:58.707 --> 12:00.413
Even if I'm not using the thing,

12:00.513 --> 12:05.393
I still don't like the thought
of someone else pounding away on it.

12:07.720 --> 12:10.216
See that?
She's working for ten minutes now.

12:10.316 --> 12:12.417
I'm actually getting some...
- I need a break!

12:12.517 --> 12:14.085
Tell me about your ex-wife.

12:14.185 --> 12:16.433
Lovely woman. Sex was good.
Crazy as hell.

12:16.533 --> 12:17.611
Back to work.

12:17.779 --> 12:21.594
So she was crazy?
I'll bet that's why the sex was good.

12:21.694 --> 12:22.994
Why'd she leave?

12:23.120 --> 12:25.590
