14:57.563 --> 14:59.762
I feel like things have gotten weird
since I moved in,

14:59.862 --> 15:03.633
and I think I know why.
Maybe we should talk about it.

15:03.733 --> 15:05.578
I'd like to.
I can't.

15:06.529 --> 15:10.089
I'm in the middle of... Something.
So... Darn it.

15:16.040 --> 15:17.248
Christmas was great

15:17.348 --> 15:19.819
'cause it was a real white Christmas.
It was just awesome.

15:19.919 --> 15:21.989
This polymer should plug the leak,

15:22.089 --> 15:23.570
but it's a temporary fix.

15:23.670 --> 15:25.477
Unless we figure out
why it's leaking,

15:25.577 --> 15:29.857
it's gonna keep happening.
- Look at that gorgeous creature.

15:30.179 --> 15:33.199
I have to stop him
from getting my girl.

15:34.159 --> 15:36.478
God. Lem, you're using science
for no good.

15:36.578 --> 15:39.631
We took an oath
we would try to do that less.

15:39.731 --> 15:43.156
I'm cranking this all the way up.
I'll bet brody is a lot less suave

15:43.256 --> 15:46.876
when he's covered in his own vomit.
I know I am!

15:51.154 --> 15:52.393
That's gross.

15:53.369 --> 15:56.516
Oh, my god, I emptied
the stomach of the woman I love.

15:56.616 --> 15:58.451
Okay, fellas, time's up.

15:58.576 --> 16:00.694
We're gonna go fix the biocomputer.
Follow me.

16:00.794 --> 16:02.613
But the polymer
still needs more testing.

16:02.713 --> 16:05.500
If you come with me now, I won't ask
what you did to that poor woman...

16:05.600 --> 16:07.880
To make her throw up like that.

16:08.009 --> 16:09.259
Fair enough.

16:10.446 --> 16:11.469
My god...

16:12.175 --> 16:13.534
It's beautiful.

16:15.364 --> 16:18.324
Half computer,
half living organic matter.

16:19.243 --> 16:20.743
That looks like barf.

16:21.979 --> 16:23.091
I Miss lucy.

16:23.941 --> 16:26.005
I just want to shoot
this thing full of polymer

