Since it hasn't been tested,
there's a 20% chance

16:31.778 --> 16:34.492
that when the polymer interacts
with the corrosive acids,

16:34.592 --> 16:36.754
the entire thing could explode.

16:37.399 --> 16:38.714
Let's see, 20%...

16:39.123 --> 16:42.683
And there's a 100% chance
Linda's still in my office.

16:42.783 --> 16:44.603
Let's do it.
Stand back!

16:50.383 --> 16:52.929
There was a 1-in-5 chance
that this could end badly,

16:53.029 --> 16:58.569
but that was a chance I was willing
to take to get my life back to normal.

16:58.643 --> 16:59.415
Wait!

17:00.336 --> 17:02.013
I know what's causing the problem.

17:02.113 --> 17:06.393
The biocomputer has an ulcer.
That's why it's leaking fluid.

17:06.510 --> 17:09.238
This thing has been running nonstop
for three years.

17:09.338 --> 17:12.008
It's stressed.
But since it's a biocomputer,

17:12.108 --> 17:13.858
instead of crashing like a machine,

17:13.959 --> 17:16.545
it's secreting acids
like a living organism.

17:16.645 --> 17:18.048
How do you know that?

17:18.147 --> 17:21.528
I realized it
when I saw you chugging antacid.

17:23.798 --> 17:26.464
I guess I've also been under
a lot of pressure.

17:26.564 --> 17:28.992
With Linda moving in my office
and all, it's...

17:29.092 --> 17:31.012
It's been a difficult time.

17:31.610 --> 17:32.930
So what do we do?

17:33.227 --> 17:34.274
We're men.

17:34.399 --> 17:38.170
We ignore your vulnerable moment.
- I meant about the biocomputer.

17:38.270 --> 17:41.139
All it needs is a way to communicate
when it's stressed.

17:41.239 --> 17:43.767
I can write a program
that's triggered by an acid buildup,

17:43.867 --> 17:47.487
a sort of acid interface,
or "ass-face" for short.

17:48.550 --> 17:53.730
I'm not sure these abbreviations
are really worth the time they're saving

17:53.781 --> 17:55.451
As much as I hate to admit it,

17:55.551 --> 17:57.361
we have something in common.

17:57.461 --> 18:00.033
We both get stressed out
when we don't communicate.

18:00.133 --> 18:04.533
Plus, I'm pretty sure neither of us
can fold a fitted sheet.

18:04.731 --> 18:05.931
We need to talk.

18:06.397 --> 18:09.528
Not now, Ted. I'm working.
- Now you're working?

18:09.628 --> 18:12.768
I've got this report due tomorrow,
remember?

18:13.891 --> 18:17.091
But, fine, what did you want
to talk about?

18:17.407 --> 18:20.187
Your work habits
and how bad they are

18:20.239 --> 18:22.159
and how much that bugs me.

18:23.430 --> 18:25.250
This can wait.
Go ahead.

18:26.535 --> 18:29.495
To begin with,
your work habits are bad.

18:29.723 --> 18:32.003
And in conclusion, that bugs me.

18:32.756 --> 18:35.016
That's not why you've been so tense.

18:35.116 --> 18:37.576
You know why you've been so tense?

18:38.407 --> 18:40.561
Does it have anything
to do with your workabits?

18:40.661 --> 18:42.661
Damn.
- You still want me.

18:42.800 --> 18:44.555
I'm in your staring place,

18:44.655 --> 18:46.963
but you're still too wounded
by your ex-wife leaving you

18:47.063 --> 18:49.465
to know what to do with that.
So you don't want to be with me

18:49.565 --> 18:51.391
because you're afraid
I might leave, too.

18:51.491 --> 18:53.946
You flirt with me,
you stare at my butt,

18:54.046 --> 18:57.343
but that's as far as you can go.
- As far as I can go? You flirt, too.

18:57.443 --> 19:00.396
You're the one that has a boyfriend.
- You're the one that has a...

19:00.496 --> 19:02.476
Good... that's a good point.

19:02.609 --> 19:04.495
But six weeks ago,
I did not have a boyfriend,

19:04.595 --> 19:07.055
and you still wouldn't be with me.

19:07.343 --> 19:10.213
Fine. From now on, no more flirting.

19:10.338 --> 19:12.018
We keep it professional.

19:12.128 --> 19:13.818
Fine with me... boss.

19:13.987 --> 19:14.738
Good.

19:15.143 --> 19:17.724
Starting now,
you're just another butt-less coworker.

19:17.824 --> 19:18.555
Good.

19:18.680 --> 19:22.240
Then the door has nothing
to hit on my way out.

19:32.629 --> 19:35.519
I found your sweater in the lab,
so I had it dry-cleaned.

19:35.619 --> 19:37.179
That was nice of you.

19:38.362 --> 19:40.822
Listen, lucy, about what happened...

19:40.972 --> 19:43.932
Look, it's the exotic dude
from the lab.

19:45.557 --> 19:47.557
Come on, babe.
Tea's ready.

19:48.651 --> 19:49.451
Sorry.

19:50.126 --> 19:52.748
I thought he was a jerk at first,
but then when I threw up,

19:52.848 --> 19:55.808
he brought me home
and took care of me.

19:55.943 --> 19:56.843
Weird?

19:57.771 --> 20:01.631
If I hadn't gotten sick,
this never would've happened.

20:02.888 --> 20:05.848
So you owe me $12
for the dry cleaning.

20:06.271 --> 20:08.183
Thanks to Phil,
the biocomputer healed

20:08.283 --> 20:10.386
and was brought back
to the land of the half-living.

20:10.486 --> 20:14.906
More importantly, everyone could
go back to their own work spaces.

20:15.006 --> 20:17.226
<i>For some, it was bittersweet.</i>

20:19.661 --> 20:21.901
You'll always have
your sneeze-related head injury.

20:22.001 --> 20:23.012
<i>For others,</i>

20:23.180 --> 20:26.860
<i>getting their office back
was julie-andrews sweet.</i>

20:31.229 --> 20:33.976
You did this, Phil.
And to recognize your efforts,

20:34.076 --> 20:36.802
we're promoting you
to senior lab associate.

20:36.902 --> 20:39.422
I was promoted to that a year ago.

20:39.502 --> 20:40.415
Really?

20:40.781 --> 20:43.921
You shouldn't have been.
You probably owe the company some money.

20:44.021 --> 20:46.121
I'll check into that for you.

20:47.432 --> 20:48.432
Thank you.

20:52.062 --> 20:54.561
Here are the test results
for the sound transmitter.

20:54.661 --> 20:56.080
Your presentation is at 3:00,

20:56.180 --> 20:58.418
you have a few hours to look it over.
- Thank you.

20:58.518 --> 21:00.198
Very professionally done.

21:00.272 --> 21:03.802
My process is just different than yours,
but I am professional,

21:03.902 --> 21:07.228
and I believe professionalism
is our new mandate?

21:07.328 --> 21:10.128
Thank you letting me share your office,
and good afternoon.

21:10.228 --> 21:11.479
Good afternoon.

